==Notes==
{{notelist}}
* {{note label|FGpercent|a|a}} Shooting percentages in basketball are calculated by taking the number of field goals, three-pointers, or free throws attempted, and dividing it by the corresponding number of shots taken.
*{{note label|3ot|b|b}}A regulation NBA game is 48 minutes long.

